Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease 2 baking sheets. In a large bowl, cream the shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in the coffee. Gradually blend in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in raisins if using. Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart on cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool on wire racks.